Sentencas: The nickel-zirconia cermet is widely used as an anode of solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: Electrochemical and microstructural properties of Ni-(Y2O3)0.08(ZrO2)0.92-(Ce0.9Gd0.1)O1.95 anode-supported microtubular solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: On the other hand, the nickel-ceria based anode indicates high electrochemical activity for hydrogen oxidation and hydrocarbon reforming.
Titulo: Electrochemical and microstructural properties of Ni-(Y2O3)0.08(ZrO2)0.92-(Ce0.9Gd0.1)O1.95 anode-supported microtubular solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In this study, electrochemical and microstructural properties of microtubular SOFCs with Ni-based composite anodes containing yttria-stabilized zirconia (YSZ) and gadolinia-doped ceria (GDC) are investigated electrochemically using impedance spectroscopy (EIS) and microstructurally using focused ion beam-scanning electron microscopy (FIB-SEM).
Titulo: Electrochemical and microstructural properties of Ni-(Y2O3)0.08(ZrO2)0.92-(Ce0.9Gd0.1)O1.95 anode-supported microtubular solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The solid solution of YSZ and GDC was easily formed after mechanical mixing and sintering at 1400 degrees C.
Titulo: Electrochemical and microstructural properties of Ni-(Y2O3)0.08(ZrO2)0.92-(Ce0.9Gd0.1)O1.95 anode-supported microtubular solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The electrical conductivity and mechanical strength for the Ni-YSZGDC composite anodes are low relative to Ni-YSZ due to poor sinterability.
Titulo: Electrochemical and microstructural properties of Ni-(Y2O3)0.08(ZrO2)0.92-(Ce0.9Gd0.1)O1.95 anode-supported microtubular solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The GDC-containing anodes show improved electrochemical activity for hydrogen oxidation, despite having lower three-phase boundary densities.
Titulo: Electrochemical and microstructural properties of Ni-(Y2O3)0.08(ZrO2)0.92-(Ce0.9Gd0.1)O1.95 anode-supported microtubular solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Distribution of relaxation times (DRT) analysis of the EIS data shows that the concentration polarization is lower for the Ni-GDC anode, due to a higher measured pore volume.
Titulo: Electrochemical and microstructural properties of Ni-(Y2O3)0.08(ZrO2)0.92-(Ce0.9Gd0.1)O1.95 anode-supported microtubular solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The maximum power density for the cell with the Ni-YSZGDC composite anode was higher than those with the Ni-YSZ and Ni-GDC anodes.
Titulo: Electrochemical and microstructural properties of Ni-(Y2O3)0.08(ZrO2)0.92-(Ce0.9Gd0.1)O1.95 anode-supported microtubular solid oxide fuel cells
